{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771615065,"nonce":"8Pnyt9vG4u8v1KmozsjDLym4gwM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87soXFQ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/247","origin":"github"},"title":"fix: harden worktree rules — prohibit editing tracked files in main tree","message":"## Problem\n\nThe current CLAUDE.md rules say \"never commit to main\" and \"all changes via PRs,\" but these are end-of-pipeline guards. Two agents independently violated the workflow by editing tracked files directly in the main worktree — one editing CLAUDE.md, the other editing multiple files (.gitignore, Makefile, README.md, CLAUDE.md). The violations started at **edit time**, not commit time.\n\nIn a multi-agent workspace, dirty state in the main tree creates conflicts between concurrent agents. The worktree system exists to prevent this, but the rules don't make that explicit early enough.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nAdd a hard rule at the top of the workflow — before any code is written — that applies to both workspace and project repos:\n\n\u003e **Never modify tracked files in the main worktree (workspace or project repos).** Before editing any tracked file, create and enter a worktree. The main tree must stay clean so other agents can branch from it.\n\n### Scope\n\nThis rule must appear in:\n- **Workspace instructions**: CLAUDE.md, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.agent/AI_RULES.md`, `.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md`\n- **Project repo instructions**: `.agents/README.md` files in project repos (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy`)\n\n### Placement\n\nThe rule should be positioned **before** the worktree workflow section, not buried inside it. It needs to be visible at the point where an agent is about to start making changes — not as an afterthought near commit rules.\n\n### Exceptions\n\n- Untracked/gitignored files (scratchpad, generated skills, etc.) are fine to edit in the main tree\n- Read-only operations (search, grep, read) are always safe anywhere\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}